items.name: RCA Cambio 10.1" 2in1 Tablet 32GB Intel Atom Z3735F Quad-Core Processor Windows 8.1
items.categoryPath: Electronics/Computers/Laptops/Shop Laptops by Type/All Laptop Computers
items.shortDescription: The RCA 10.1" 2-In-1 Tablet Quad Core offers an array of applications that will help you connect to your world on the go. Microsoft's Windows 8.1 operating system lets you complete important tasks and navigate your device with ease. Connect with friends and family on the built-in webcams. This 32gb tablet comes with a detachable keyboard, giving it the functionality of a laptop PC. A secure latching system makes it easy to enjoy the device in a variety of forms. Prop it up for viewing a movie with friends, or remove the keyboard altogether for a touch-only experience. Your Windows 8.1 tablet comes with 32gb of storage, giving you ample room for your favorite apps, photos and music. A micro-SD card slot lets you expand available memory to fit your needs. The RCA 10.1" 2-In-1 Tablet Quad Core combines versatile hardware with the power of Windows to help you manage your digital life anywhere.
items.longDescription: <br>Eligible for <b>FREE</b> Windows 10 upgrade, coming soon.<br><b>RCA W101 with WiFi 10.1" Touchscreen Tablet PC:</b><br><b>Technical Specifications:</b><ul><li>1.83GHz Intel Quad-Core processor</li><li>1GB DDR3L of system memory</li><li>32gb Tablet with 10.1" touchscreen, 1280 x 800 resolution</li><li>Built-in 802.11b/g/n WiFi and Bluetooth</li></ul><b>Additional Features:</b><ul><li>Back 2MP webcam and front 2MP webcam</li><li>USB 2.0 port, microUSB 2.0 port, microHDMI port, headphone jack</li><li>32GB onboard storage memory, additional memory via microSD card slot</li><li>Up to 6 hours of run time on a full charge</li><li>Weighs 2 lbs 29 oz</li></ul><b>Software and Applications:</b><ul><li>Windows 8.1 OS</li><li>Office Personal 365</li><li>Media formats: popular media formats</li></ul><b>What's in the Box:</b><ul><li>Tablet, battery, owner's manual and AC adapter</li></ul><br><b>What's a Tablet PC?</b><br>Tablet PCs are compact, ultra-portable entertainment devices that let you read email, surf the Internet, read eBooks, view photos, play games, listen to music and watch video files. Most tablets are based on a smaller operating system, which allows you to purchase and download additional applications from supported stores. Tablet PCs do not have a CD/DVD drive. Tablet PCs function as a secondary device for casual entertainment purposes, and are not meant to replace a computer. They are ideal for use around the home and on the go with WiFi or 3-4G mobile broadband connections (pay as you go, contract may be required for service).
